The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Thursday, June 02, 2005 

 Laggards put on notice 

 OUR BUREAU

 June 1: The board of secondary education today issued an ultimatum to a Nadia school where all 10 examinees, including the managing committee secretarys daughter, failed to clear this years Madhyamik. 

 The authorities of Hat Chapra Girls School, 125 km from Calcutta, have been asked to improve performance by next year. Or else, the schools affiliation will be cancelled. 

 A similar notice has been served on another institution ? Haranath Girls High School in Calcutta ?where all six candidates failed. In both places, guardians accused teachers of lacking in sincerity. The affiliation of a school can be cancelled if it performs poorly for three consecutive years.




